description: Tucked into a historic brownstone district in a gorgeous neighborhood, our apartment is a perfect respite after a day of touring, working or partying in the city. The express A train is two blocks and lower Manhattan is 20 minutes away, Times Square is 35-40 minutes.  And our cute little enclave has lively jazz bars, pizza joints and soul food within blocks. This isn't the neighborhood you'd want to stay in if you're looking for a scene, but it's truly a gem of classic Brooklyn. Our building is on a tree-lined block in the heart of brownstone Brooklyn. The house was built around 1904 and still holds much of its original charm, though at the time of its construction it was a one-family home. (Many of the other homes on our street still amazing house only one family!)   The guest bedroom is fitted with a full-size bed and a storage cabinet stocked with towels, toiletries and refreshments. description: We love our comfy home and are excited to offer it up for the holidays. Across from a park with beautiful gardens, Cloisters Museum, and fantastic views of the Hudson; great local spots for wining and dining; steps from a subway express to downtown. With a 1,000 sq ft of homey and comfy vibes, our apt is a great space to unwind, cook/eat in, and recharge for more adventures in the city. It's also family-friendly with a crib in the bedroom and most baby items available if needed for little ones.  We also have a large couch and queen-size air mattress if you need sleeping for more than two. We will be available by text/call/email for any questions during the entire stay. We're nestled between Washington Heights and Inwood neighborhoods. It's very safe with lots of culture and plenty of great watering holes. Our favorite thing is the fantastic parks (Fort Tryon & Inwood Hill) with stunning views. And with great access to two subway lines it's easy to get to and from anywhere in Manhattan.
